        "client_msg_id": "F9C963A8-7AE7-4B42-BE02-9D84B76DD7A9",
        "text": "This week, I'm learning more WebGPU, since I'm hoping to use it for a handful of visual programming projects down the road. I'm also still looking at options for <https:\/\/futureofcoding.slack.com\/archives\/CEXED56UR\/p1719244290391599|moving away from slack>. Would love to find something that feels more like a forum than a chat, but not toooo much like a phpbb, and doesn't have a per-user cost, and doesn't impose a maintenance burden, and is accessible to search engines (and accessible to all people, natch), and isn't likely to \"incredible journey\" or \"we AI'd every text field for you\" etc. So we're currently whatever the opposite of \"spoiled for choice\" is :)",
